com.gedcom.parser
Class GedcomToXML

java.lang.Object
  com.gedcom.parser.GedcomToXML

public class GedcomToXML
extends java.lang.Object

The GedcomToXML class represents a tool that allows to parse a GEDCOM v 5.5.1 file and generate a valid XML .

Version:
0.1
Author:
Kheireddine Ouelaa and Rachid Oubraim

setIndividuals

private void setIndividuals(org.gedcom4j.model.Individual i)
Manage an individual person : names, titles, sex, family's reference to which he belongs

Parameters:
i - : An individual person. Corresponds to the INDIVIDUAL_RECORD structure in the GEDCOM specification.

setFamilyIndividuals

private void setFamilyIndividuals(org.gedcom4j.model.Family f)
Manage individuals persons of a family : husband, wife and children.
Generate individuals XML elements :
fam : Family's tag to which the individual person belongs. Ans his attribute id
husb : Husband's tag with his attribute ref reference an existing individual person
wife : Wife's tag with his attribute ref reference an existing individual person
chil : Child's tag with his attribute ref reference an existing individual person

Parameters:
f - : A family record. Corresponds to FAM_RECORD in the GEDCOM spec.
See Also:
setFamilyEvents(Family), setMultimedia(Element, Multimedia)

setIndivividualEvents

private void setIndivividualEvents(org.gedcom4j.model.Individual i)
Manage events of an individual person : Birthday, Death, Burial, Christening .
Generate individuals XML elements :
birt : Birthday's tag
deat : Death's tag
buri : Burial's tag
chr : Christening's tag

Parameters:
i - : An individual person. Corresponds to the INDIVIDUAL_RECORD structure in the GEDCOM specification.
See Also:
setEventDate(Element, StringWithCustomTags), setEventPlace(Element, Place)

setFamilyEvents

private void setFamilyEvents(org.gedcom4j.model.Family f)
Manage family's events : Marriage and Divorce.
Generate family's events XML elements :
marr : Marriage
div : Divorce and his attribute isDiv(Y or N)

See Also:
